HEADWORD: Cupric
<hw>Cu"pric</hw> <pr>(k?"pr?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Cuprum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
derived from, copper; containing copper; -- said of those compounds of
copper in which this element is present in its lowest
proportion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cupriferous</ent>⟦br⟧
